- http://localhost/erlang/doc/doc/tutorial/c_port.html#4

1. Compile the java and erlang code.

    unix> javac port.java && erlc complex2.erl

2. Run the example (in erl shell).

    1> complex2:start(os:find_executable("java"), ["-cp", ".", "port"]).
    <0.34.0>
    2> complex2:foo(3).
    4
    3> complex2:bar(5).
    10
    4> complex2:stop().
    stop

3. using BIF port_command.

    1> Port = open_port({spawn_executable, os:find_executable("java")}, [{packet, 4}, binary, {args, ["-cp", ".", "port"]}]).
    #Port<0.424>
    2> port_command(Port, <<1,3>>).
    true
    3> flush().
    Shell got {#Port<0.424>,{data,<<4>>}}
    ok
